Shell export.env fileMCP JSON config <pre><code>export GRAPHBASE_NEO4J_URI=bolt://my-host:7687
export GRAPHBASE_NEO4J_PASSWORD=my-secret
graphbase-memories-mcp serve
</code></pre> <p>Create a <code>.env</code> file in your working directory:</p> <pre><code>GRAPHBASE_NEO4J_URI=bolt://my-host:7687
GRAPHBASE_NEO4J_USER=neo4j
GRAPHBASE_NEO4J_PASSWORD=my-secret
GRAPHBASE_NEO4J_DATABASE=neo4j
</code></pre> <p><code>pydantic-settings</code> loads <code>.env</code> files automatically if <code>python-dotenv</code> is installed.</p> <p>Pass variables via the <code>env</code> block in <code>.mcp.json</code>:</p> <pre><code>{
  "mcpServers": {
    "graphbase-memories": {
      "command": "/path/to/.venv/bin/graphbase-memories-mcp",
      "args": ["serve"],
      "env": {
        "GRAPHBASE_NEO4J_URI": "bolt://localhost:7687",
        "GRAPHBASE_NEO4J_USER": "neo4j",
        "GRAPHBASE_NEO4J_PASSWORD": "graphbase"
      }
    }
  }
}
</code></pre>
